@node Introduction "Introduction"
@{fg shine}
              File Checker V3.00 - By: John White - Public Domain.
             ------------------------------------------------------

@{fg text}
 File_Checker V3.00 is a small program that checks your LGUI Speech Files
 and LGUI Language Files for common mistakes - Not all mistakes though
 simply because of the nature of LGUI files being in ASCII format. Which
 means LGUI programs/files are not fool proof. Hence the need for a program
 such as this.

 File_Checker V3.00 needs at least Operating System 39 to work. If you
 are going to use the TRANSLATE ToolType/Keyword you will also need the
 Translator.Library (V37+).
@{fg shine}
 General Notes@{fg text}

 * You can redirect the Output from FILE_CHECKER to a file, so that you
   can use a text editor to Cut `N' Paste any Language Text that has been
   translated into Phonetic Text. For example:

     FILE_CHECKER DEVICE_LOADFROM WORK: TRANSLATE TRUE Ram:My_File

   The above would use the Keywords and their Arguments as expected and then
   put any translated Language Text, which would now be Phonetic Text, into
   the file Ram:My_File
@{fg shine}
